modules.description: Provides functions to manipulate and inspect network flow data structures, including packet parsing, header extraction, and state tracking. Works with custom types representing network packets, flow states, and protocol-specific data. Used to implement protocol handlers and traffic analysis in Mirage-based network applications.

Provides functions to read from and write to network flows, with support for handling errors and shutting down connections. Operates on `Cstruct.t` buffers and custom error types for read and write operations. Used to manage data transmission in network protocols, ensuring proper handling of connection closure and error recovery.
